A9. Discover Privacy Technique Used Online

For this activity, I explored privacy techniques implemented on social media platforms. The example I chose is the private account feature on Instagram.
When a user sets their Instagram account to private, their posts, stories, and other content are hidden from people who are not approved followers. 
Only users who the account owner has accepted as followers can view the private content. 
This feature gives users control over who can access their personal information and content online.

How to Enable the Private Account Feature:
1. Open your Instagram profile and click on the three lines (menu) in the top-right corner.
2. Go to Settings → Privacy → Account Privacy.
3. Toggle the Private Account option to enable or disable privacy.

This featur is a privacy techneque because:
Users can restrict access to personal posts and information, ensuring that only approved followers can view them.
The account owner decides who can access their content, enhancing privacy on the platform.
This reduces the risk of unauthorized viewing, sharing, or misuse of personal information
